wxWidgets Mutabor GUI

While the original frontend of Mutabor was designed using Borland OWL the current one uses the platform independent environment provided by wxWidgets. Mehr ...

Ausführliche Beschreibung

While the original frontend of Mutabor was designed using Borland OWL the current one uses the platform independent environment provided by wxWidgets. 

Noch zu erledigen:
remove this file: a character set error implies that the whole file has to be reconverted.

  393         void MutApp::OnInitCmdLine(wxCmdLineParser&  parser) {
  394                 const wxCmdLineEntryDesc cmdLineDesc[] = {
  395                         { wxCMD_LINE_PARAM,  NULL, NULL, _("logic file"),
  396                           wxCMD_LINE_VAL_STRING, wxCMD_LINE_PARAM_MULTIPLE|wxCMD_LINE_PARAM_OPTIONAL },
  397                         { wxCMD_LINE_NONE, "", "", "", wxCMD_LINE_VAL_NONE, 0 }
  398                 };
  399 
  400                 wxApp::OnInitCmdLine(parser);
  401                 parser.SetDesc(cmdLineDesc);
  402 
  403 #ifdef DEBUG
  404                 InitDebugCommandLine(parser);
  405 #endif
  406 
  407 
  408         }
  409 
  410         bool MutApp::OnCmdLineParsed(wxCmdLineParser&  parser) {
  411                 if (!wxApp::OnCmdLineParsed(parser)) return false;
  412 #ifdef DEBUG
  413                 ProcessDebugCommandLine(parser);
  414 #endif
  415                 wxString str;
  416                 int count = parser.GetParamCount();
  417                 for (int i = 0; i<count;i++)
  418                 {
  419                         // we have a document to open
  420                         str = parser.GetParam(i);
  421                         DEBUGLOG (always, "cmd line param: %s\n" , WXSTRINGCAST(str));
  422                         // this will probably see if the file exists, and has the right extension
  423 
  424 //              MutFrame * frame = CreateMainFrame(EditorMenu);
  425 //              frame->OpenFile(str);
  426 
  427                         if (document_manager)
  428                                 document_manager->CreateDocument(str, wxDOC_SILENT);
  429                 }
  430 
  431                 DEBUGLOG (other, "Command line parsed." );
  432                 return true;
  433         }

  435         void MutApp::OnUnhandledException() {
  436                 try {
  437                         throw;
  438                 } catch (const std::exception & e) {
  439                         std::cerr << "Unhandled exception: " << e.what() << std::endl <<
  440                                 boost::current_exception_diagnostic_information();
  441                 } catch(...) {
  442                         std::cerr << "Unhandled exception!" << std::endl <<
  443                                 boost::current_exception_diagnostic_information();
  444                 }
  445 #ifdef DEBUG
  446                 abort();
  447 #endif
  448         }
  449         bool MutApp::OnExceptionInMainLoop() {
  450                 try {
  451                         throw;
  452                 } catch (const std::exception & e) {
  453                         std::cerr << "Unhandled exception: " << e.what() << std::endl <<
  454                                 boost::current_exception_diagnostic_information();
  455                 } catch(...) {
  456                         std::cerr << "Unhandled exception!" << std::endl <<
  457                                 boost::current_exception_diagnostic_information();
  458                 }
  459 #ifdef DEBUG
  460                 abort();
  461 #endif
  462                 return true; // continue
  463         }
  464         void MutApp::OnFatalException() {
  465                 try {
  466                         throw;
  467                 } catch (const std::exception & e) {
  468                         std::cerr << "Unhandled exception: " << e.what() << std::endl <<
  469                                 boost::current_exception_diagnostic_information();
  470                 } catch(...) {
  471                         std::cerr << "Unhandled exception!" << std::endl <<
  472                                 boost::current_exception_diagnostic_information();
  473                 }
  474 #ifdef DEBUG
  475                 abort();
  476 #endif
  477         }

  479 #ifdef DEBUG
  480         void MutApp::OnAssertFailure(const wxChar *file,
  481                                     int line,
  482                                     const wxChar *func,
  483                                     const wxChar *cond,
  484                                     const wxChar *msg)
  485         {
  486                 mutabor_assert_fail(wxConvUTF8.cWX2MB(file),
  487                                     line,
  488                                     wxConvUTF8.cWX2MB(func),
  489                                     wxConvUTF8.cWX2MB(cond),
  490                                     wxConvUTF8.cWX2MB(msg));
  491         }
  492 #endif

  496 // Extend event processing to search the view's event table
  497         bool MutApp::ProcessEvent(wxEvent& event)
  498         {
  499                 bool retval =  wxApp::ProcessEvent(event);
  500 #ifdef DEBUG
  501                 if (!retval) {
  502                         DEBUGLOG(eventqueue,
  503                                  ("Unhandled event %p, id=%d, type=%d"),
  504                                  static_cast<void *>(&event),
  505                                  (int)(event.GetId()),
  506                                  (int)(event.GetEventType())
  507                                 );
  508                 }
  509 #endif
  510                 return retval;
  511         }
  512 #if 0
  513         // may be removed
  514         void MutApp::PassEventToDocManagerCMD(wxCommandEvent& event)
  515         {
  516                 DEBUGLOG (eventqueue, "Command %p, id=%d, type=%d" ,
  517                          static_cast<void *>(&event),
  518                          event.GetId(),
  519                          (int)event.GetEventType()
  520                         );
  521                 if (!(document_manager->ProcessEvent(event)))
  522                         event.Skip();
  523         }
  524         void MutApp::PassEventToDocManagerUPD(wxUpdateUIEvent& event)
  525         {
  526                 DEBUGLOG (eventqueue, "UpdateUI: %p, id=%d, type=%d" ,
  527                          static_cast<void *>(&event),
  528                          event.GetId(),
  529                          (int)event.GetEventType()
  530                         );
  531                 if (!(document_manager->ProcessEvent(event)))
  532                         event.Skip();
  533         }
  534 #endif
  535         void MutApp::OnMRUFile(wxCommandEvent& event)
  536         {
  537                 int n = event.GetId() - wxID_FILE1;  // the index in MRU list
  538                 wxString filename(document_manager->GetHistoryFile(n));
  539                 if ( !filename.empty() )
  540                 {
  541                         // verify that the file exists before doing anything else
  542                         if ( wxFile::Exists(filename) )
  543                         {
  544                                 // try to open it
  545                                 if (!document_manager->CreateDocument(filename, wxDOC_SILENT))
  546                                 {
  547                                         // remove the file from the MRU list. The user should already be notified.
  548                                         document_manager->RemoveFileFromHistory(n);
  549 
  550                                         wxLogError(_("The file '%s' couldn't be opened.\nIt has been removed from the most recently used files list."),
  551                                                    filename.c_str());
  552                                 } else {
  553                                         wxView * v = document_manager->GetCurrentView();
  554                                         if (v) {
  555                                                 wxWindow * w = v->GetFrame();
  556                                                 if (w) {
  557                                                         w->Raise();
  558                                                 }
  559                                         }
  560                                 }
  561                         }
  562                         else
  563                         {
  564                                 // remove the bogus filename from the MRU list and notify the user
  565                                 // about it
  566                                 document_manager->RemoveFileFromHistory(n);
  567 
  568                                 wxLogError(_("The file '%s' doesn't exist and couldn't be opened.\nIt has been removed from the most recently used files list."),
  569                                            filename.c_str());
  570                         }
  571                 }
  572         }

  712         MutFrame* MutApp::CreateMainFrame(MenuType type, wxWindowID id)
  713         {

  716                                                wxDefaultPosition, wxDefaultSize, //wxSize(500, 400),

  722         // Give it an icon
  723         MutFrame* MutApp::InitMainFrame(MenuType type, MutFrame * frame)
  724         {
  725 #ifdef __WXMSW__
  726                 frame->SetIcon(wxIcon(_T("mutabor_icn")));
  727 #else
  728                 frame->SetIcon(wxIcon( mutabor_xpm ));
  729 #endif
  730 
  731                 // Make a menubar
  732 
  733                 wxMenuBar *menuBar = new wxMenuBar;
  734                 frame->SetFileMenu(MakeFileMenu(menuBar, type));
  735                 MakeEditMenu(menuBar, type);
  736                 MakeViewMenu(menuBar, type);
  737                 MakeLogicMenu(menuBar);
  738                 MakeRoutesMenu(menuBar, type);
  739                 MakeSequencerMenu(menuBar);
  740                 MakeHelpMenu(menuBar);
  741 
  742                 // Associate the menu bar with the frame
  743                 frame->SetMenuBar(menuBar);
  744 
  745 #if wxUSE_STATUSBAR
  746                 frame->CreateStatusBar();
  747 #endif // wxUSE_STATUSBAR
  748 
  749                 return frame;
  750         }

  752         void MutApp::CmFileNew (wxCommandEvent& event)
  753         {
  754                 mutUnused(event);
  755                 STUBC;
  756                 return;
  757 # if 0
  758 #ifdef DEBUG
  759                 printf("MutApp::CmFileNew\n");
  760 #endif
  761                 MutFrame * frame = dynamic_cast<MutFrame*>(GetTopWindow());
  762 
  763                 if (MustOpenFrame(frame))
  764                         frame = CreateMainFrame(EditorMenu);
  765 
  766 #ifdef DEBUG

  768

  771                 frame->Show();

  831         void MutApp::CmRoutes (wxCommandEvent& event)

  859         void MutApp::ShowHelp(int commandId)
  860         {
  861                 switch (commandId) {
  862 
  863                 case CM_HELPINDEX:
  864                         HelpController->DisplayContents();
  865 
  866                         break;
  867 
  868                 case CM_HELP:
  869                         HelpController->Display(_("help.html"));
  870 
  871                         break;
  872 
  873                 case CM_SETUP:
  874                         HelpController->Display(_("The setup dialog"));
  875 
  876                         break;
  877 
  878                 case CM_HELPHANDBOOK:
  879                         HelpController->Display(_("manual.html"));
  880 
  881                         break;
  882 
  883                 case CM_HELPREFERENCE:
  884                         HelpController->Display(_("reference.html"));
  885 
  886                         break;
  887 
  888                 case CM_HELPONHELP:
  889                         HelpController->Display(_("Help window"));
  890 
  891                         break;
  892 
  893                 case CM_HELPCOMMON:
  894                         HelpController->DisplayContents();
  895 
  896                         break;
  897 
  898                 case CM_HELPSEARCH: {
  899                         wxString key = wxGetTextFromUser(_("Search for?"),
  900                                                          _("Search help for keyword"),
  901                                                          wxEmptyString,
  902                                                          GetTopWindow());
  903 
  904                         if (! key.IsEmpty())
  905                                 HelpController->KeywordSearch(key);
  906                 }
  907 
  908                         break;
  909                 }
  910         }

  913         void CmError(wxCommandEvent& event) {
  914                 mutabor::error_type type = (mutabor::error_type) event.GetInt();
  915                 wxString heading;
  916                 int style;
  917                 switch (type) {
  918                 case mutabor::generic_warning:
  919                 case mutabor::compiler_warning:
  920                 case mutabor::runtime_warning:
  921                         style = wxICON_WARNING;
  922                         break;
  923                 case mutabor::generic_error:
  924                 case mutabor::internal_error:
  925                 case mutabor::compiler_error:
  926                 case mutabor::runtime_error:
  927                 default:
  928                         style = wxICON_ERROR;
  929                         break;
  930                 }
  931 #if wxCHECK_VERSION(2,9,0)
  932                 heading = to_string(type);
  933 #else
  934                 heading = wxString::FromUTF8(to_string(type));
  935 #endif
  936                 wxMessageBox(event.GetString(),heading,wxOK | style);
  937         }
  938 
  939 
  940         void MutApp::CmQuit (wxCommandEvent& event)
  941         {
  942                 TRACE;
  943 
  944                 SetExitOnFrameDelete(true);
  945                 //              Exit();
  946 
  947                 if (quitting) return;
  948 
  949                 quitting = true;
  950                 event.Skip(false);
  951 
  952 
  953                 wxWindow * window;
  954                 SetTopWindow(NULL);
  955 
  956                 //      if (frames.empty()) {
  957                 if ((window = GetTopWindow()) == NULL) {
  958                         DEBUGLOG (other, "No Frames." );
  959                         quitting = false;
  960                         ExitMainLoop();
  961                         return;
  962                 }
  963 
  964                 // first check whether docmanager allows quitting
  965                 if (!document_manager->Clear(false))
  966                 {
  967                         quitting = false;
  968                         return;
  969                 }
  970 
  971 
  972                 DEBUGLOG (other, "Starting Loop" );
  973 
  974 /*      while (Pending())
  975         Dispatch();
  976 
  977 
  978         DEBUGLOG (other, "Dispatched all events" );
  979 
  980         wxIdleMode imode = wxIdleEvent::GetMode();
  981         wxIdleEvent::SetMode(wxIDLE_PROCESS_ALL);
  982 */
  983 
  984                 Yield();
  985 
  986                 /* make a copy of the top level window list as the
  987                    list may change or not, this depends on actions, we
  988                    don't have control over */
  989                 wxWindowList frames = wxTopLevelWindows;
  990 
  991                 for (wxWindowList::iterator i = frames.begin();
  992                      i!= frames.end();
  993                      i++) {
  994                         wxWindow * window = *i;
  995                         DEBUGLOG(aui,"Closing window with id %d\n",
  996                                  window->GetId());
  997                         if (wxTopLevelWindows.Find(window) == NULL)
  998                                 continue;
  999                         {
 1000                                 // On Windows we get an SEGV when we delete panes directly without detaching.
 1001                                 // So we have two choices: find the panes and detach them or delete their
 1002                                 // managed frame instead, leaving the cleaning to wxAuiManager.
 1003                                 // We choose the latter.
 1004                                 wxAuiManager * manager = wxAuiManager::GetManager(window);
 1005                                 if (manager != NULL) {
 1006                                         DEBUGLOG(aui,"Not deleting window %d with title %s.",
 1007                                                  window->GetId(),
 1008                                                  (dynamic_cast<wxTopLevelWindow *>(window)?
 1009                                                   dynamic_cast<wxTopLevelWindow *>(window)->GetTitle().ToUTF8():
 1010                                                   "<not a toplevel window>"));
 1011                                         window = manager->GetManagedWindow();
 1012                                         if (!window)
 1013                                                 continue;
 1014                                 }
 1015                         }
 1016                         if (! window->Close()) {
 1017 //                      wxIdleEvent::SetMode(imode);
 1018                                 quitting = false;
 1019                                 return;
 1020                         }
 1021                         Yield();
 1022                 }
 1023 
 1024                 DEBUGLOG (other, "finished loop" );
 1025         }
 1026

 1028         void MutApp::CmPrintError (wxCommandEvent& event) {
 1029                 PrintError(event.GetInt(),event.GetString());
 1030         }

 1032         void MutApp::PrintError(int type, const wxString & s, wxWindow * parent) {
 1033 #if wxCHECK_VERSION(2,9,0)
 1034                 wxString head(mutabor::to_string((mutabor::error_type)type));
 1035 #else
 1036                 wxString head=wxString::FromUTF8(mutabor::to_string((mutabor::error_type)type));
 1037 #endif
 1038                 int style = wxOK | wxCENTRE;
 1039                 switch (type) {
 1040         case mutabor::compiler_warning:
 1041         case mutabor::runtime_warning:
 1042         case mutabor::generic_warning:
 1043                 style |= wxICON_EXCLAMATION;
 1044                 break;
 1045         case mutabor::generic_error:
 1046         case mutabor::internal_error:
 1047         case mutabor::compiler_error:
 1048         case mutabor::runtime_error:
 1049                 style |= wxICON_ERROR;
 1050                 break;
 1051         default:
 1052                 style |= wxICON_INFORMATION;
 1053         }
 1054                 wxMessageDialog * dialog  = new wxMessageDialog (parent?parent:GetTopWindow(), s, head, style);
 1055                 dialog->ShowModal();
 1056                 dialog->Destroy();
 1057 
 1058         }

 1061         wxString MutApp::GetResourceName(const wxString & file)
 1062         {
 1063 #ifdef MUTABOR_TEST
 1064                 wxFileName rcname(file);
 1065                 wxString dir = rcname.GetPath();
 1066                 wxChar sep = rcname.GetPathSeparator();
 1067                 if (dir.empty())
 1068                         rcname.SetPath(wxString::FromUTF8(srcdir));
 1069                 else
 1070                         rcname.SetPath(wxString::FromUTF8(srcdir) + sep + dir);
 1071                 if (rcname.IsFileReadable()) {
 1072                         return rcname.GetFullPath();
 1073                 }
 1074                 if (dir.empty())
 1075                         rcname.SetPath(wxString::FromUTF8(top_srcdir));
 1076                 else
 1077                         rcname.SetPath(wxString::FromUTF8(top_srcdir) + sep + dir);
 1078                 if (rcname.IsFileReadable()) {
 1079                         return rcname.GetFullPath();
 1080                 }
 1081                 rcname.SetPath(wxString::FromUTF8(top_srcdir) + _T("/Images/Icons/png/"));
 1082                 if (dir.empty())
 1083                         rcname.SetPath(wxString::FromUTF8(top_srcdir) + _T("/Images/Icons/png/"));
 1084                 else
 1085                         rcname.SetPath(wxString::FromUTF8(top_srcdir) + _T("/Images/Icons/png/") + dir);
 1086                 if (rcname.IsFileReadable()) {
 1087                         return rcname.GetFullPath();
 1088                 }
 1089                 std::cout << (const char *)rcname.GetFullPath().ToUTF8() << std::endl;
 1090                 return file;
 1091 
 1092 #else
 1093 
 1094                 const wxLocale * m_locale = wxGetLocale();
 1095                 wxStandardPathsBase & sp = wxStandardPaths::Get();
 1096                 wxString localename = m_locale->GetCanonicalName();
 1097                 wxFileName relativename(file);
 1098                 wxFileName rcname(relativename);
 1099                 rcname.MakeAbsolute(sp.GetLocalizedResourcesDir(localename));
 1100                 DEBUGLOGTYPE(other,MutApp,("Trying do load resources...\n%s\n%s"),rcname.GetFullPath().c_str(),sp.GetResourcesDir().c_str());
 1101                 if (!rcname.IsFileReadable()) {
 1102                         rcname = relativename;
 1103                         rcname.MakeAbsolute(sp.GetLocalizedResourcesDir(localename.BeforeFirst(_T('_'))));
 1104                         DEBUGLOGTYPE(other,MutApp,("Trying %s"),rcname.GetFullPath().c_str());
 1105                         if (!rcname.IsFileReadable()) {
 1106                                 rcname = relativename;
 1107                                 rcname.MakeAbsolute(sp.GetResourcesDir());
 1108                                 DEBUGLOGTYPE(other,MutApp,("Trying %s"),rcname.GetFullPath().c_str());
 1109                         }
 1110                 }
 1111                 localename = rcname.GetFullPath();
 1112                 return localename;
 1113 #endif
 1114         }

 1486         void MutApp::SaveState()
 1487         {
 1488                 /* \todo save Parameters of all open windows */
 1489                 wxConfigBase *config = wxConfig::Get();
 1490                 if (!config) {
 1491                         wxLogError(_("Could not get configuration storage"));
 1492                         return;
 1493                 }
 1494 
 1495                 wxString oldpath = config->GetPath();
 1496 
 1497                 config->SetPath(_T("/Settings"));
 1498                 config->Write(_T("Tone system"), asTS);
 1499                 config->Write(_T("Save editor"), SaveEditor);
 1500                 config->Write(_T("Color bars"), UseColorBars);
 1501 
 1502                 config->SetPath(_T("DocManager"));
 1503                 document_manager->FileHistorySave(*config);
 1504                 config->SetPath(_T(".."));
 1505 
 1506                 SaveRoutes(config);
 1507                 config->SetPath(oldpath);
 1508         }

 1510         void MutApp::RestoreState()
 1511 
 1512         {
 1513                 /* \todo restore Windows of last session. */
 1514                 wxConfigBase *config = wxConfig::Get();
 1515                 if (!config) {
 1516                         wxLogError(_("Could not get configuration storage"));
 1517                         return;
 1518                 }
 1519 
 1520 
 1521                 // up to Version 2.9.3 the file history does not cleanup menus
 1522                 if (document_manager) {
 1523                         int max = document_manager->GetHistoryFilesCount();
 1524                         wxFileHistory * h = document_manager->GetFileHistory();
 1525                         if (h)
 1526                                 for (int i = max-1; i >= 0; i--)
 1527                                         h -> RemoveFileFromHistory(i);
 1528                 }
 1529 
 1530                 wxString oldpath = config->GetPath();
 1531 
 1532                 config->SetPath(_T("/Settings"));
 1533                 config->Read(_T("ToneSystem"), &asTS, true);
 1534                 config->Read(_T("SaveEditor"), &SaveEditor, true);
 1535                 config->Read(_T("ColorBars"), &UseColorBars, true);
 1536 
 1537                 config->SetPath(_T("DocManager"));
 1538                 document_manager->FileHistoryLoad(*config);
 1539                 config->SetPath(_T(".."));
 1540 
 1541                 MutRouteWnd * routewnd=NULL;
 1542                 MutFrame * frame =
 1543                         dynamic_cast<MutFrame*>(wxWindow::FindWindowById(WK_ROUTE));
 1544                 if (frame) {
 1545                         wxWindowList & list = frame->GetChildren();
 1546                         for (wxWindowList::iterator i = list.begin();i!= list.end();i++) {
 1547                                 routewnd = dynamic_cast<MutRouteWnd *> (*i);
 1548                                 if (routewnd) break;
 1549                         }
 1550                 }
 1551 /*              if (routewnd) {
 1552                         routewnd->ClearDevices();
 1553                 }
 1554 */
 1555                 // emty lists
 1556                 TRACE;
 1557                 RouteClass::ClearRouteList();
 1558                 TRACE;
 1559                 InputDeviceClass::ClearDeviceList();
 1560                 TRACE;
 1561                 BoxClass::ClearBoxList();
 1562                 TRACE;
 1563                 OutputDeviceClass::ClearDeviceList();
 1564                 TRACE;
 1565 
 1566                 DebugCheckRoutes();
 1567 
 1568                 LoadRoutes(config);
 1569 
 1570 
 1571                 if (routewnd) {
 1572                         routewnd->InitDevices();
 1573                         routewnd->Layout();
 1574                         routewnd->FitInside();
 1575                         routewnd->Refresh();
 1576 //                      routewnd->Update();
 1577 
 1578                 }
 1579                 DebugCheckRoutes();
 1580

 1980         {
 1981                 /* the current implementation saves unused box command
 1982                    ids for further usage.  Thus the map of command ids

Call update on a Window hierarchy recursively. 


Zu beachten
this function is very expensive. It should be called very rarly (as well as Update().
